    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "Block encoding is a method to get a quantum computer accessible to the \
information in a matrix M. Typically, the resulting bigger embedding matrix \
is denoted by U_M and has the block form U_M:=(GridBox[{{M, *}, {*, *}}]) , \
where * indicates the corresponding block is irrelevant.", "synonyms" -> {}, 
